<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <%- include('partials/head', { title: 'Privacy Policy · websidian' }) %>
</head>
<body class="landing-page">
  <header class="landing-nav">
    <a class="landing-brand" href="/">websidian</a>
    <nav class="landing-nav-actions">
      <select class="lang-select" data-lang-switch aria-label="Language" data-i18n-attr="aria-label:lang_switch">
        <option value="en">EN</option>
        <option value="de">DE</option>
      </select>
      <a class="btn-ghost" href="/" data-i18n="home">Home</a>
    </nav>
  </header>

  <main class="landing-main">
    <article class="legal">
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>

      <p class="section-lead">
        websidian is built privacy-first. We collect no personal data and we do not track
        you.
      </p>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>No personal data</h2>
        <p>
          We do not ask for, collect or store any personal data such as your real name, email
          address, phone number or location. To use the service you only choose a username and
          a password &mdash; nothing that identifies you personally is required.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>No tracking</h2>
        <p>
          There are no analytics, no advertising, no third-party trackers and no tracking
          cookies. The only cookie used is a strictly necessary session cookie that keeps you
          signed in. It is removed when you log out.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>What is stored</h2>
        <p>
          The only data stored is what is required to operate your vault:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Your chosen username and a securely hashed password.</li>
          <li>An required two-factor authentication (2FA) secret, if you enable 2FA.</li>
          <li>The notes, folders, drawings and files you create in your vault.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Your content is stored solely so the service can show it back to you. It is never
          sold, shared or analyzed.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>Encryption at rest</h2>
        <p>
          Your vault contents &mdash; notes, drawings, attachments and PDFs &mdash; are
          encrypted on the server with AES-256-GCM before they are written to disk or sent to
          object storage. Each account's data is encrypted with its own derived key, so the
          stored files are unreadable on their own.
        </p>
        <p>
          This is encryption <em>at rest</em>: it protects your data if the underlying storage
          is stolen or accessed directly. It is not zero-knowledge end-to-end encryption &mdash;
          while you are signed in, the server holds the key in memory in order to display and
          search your notes. When you use the <strong>Export</strong> feature, your vault is
          exported decrypted so you always have a portable, platform-independent backup.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>Deleting your data</h2>
        <p>
          You can delete your account at any time from the account dashboard. Deleting your
          account permanently removes your account record and all of your vault data from the
          server.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>Self-hosting</h2>
        <p>
          websidian is open source and can be self-hosted. When you self-host, you are the
          sole operator of your instance and the only party with access to its data.
        </p>
      </section>
    </article>
  </main>

  <%- include('partials/footer') %>
</body>
</html>
